Kane scoffed but didn’t deny it—too busy grinding against Hailee with a low groan when she slumped back into him. His voice came out ragged against her ear: **"Keep rubbin’ that ass on me and we ain't even *makin'* it to the hotel."** One hand slid up to fist in her hair, tilting her head back so Enzo could see the way Kane's pupils swallowed all that hazel gold. **"Tell me—you want us to ruin you right here? Or you wanna see how many times I can make you scream in that penthouse?"**

Nearby, a bouncer eyed them warily—some local muscle with Bayou Crew ink peeking from his collar. Enzo caught the look and flashed him a mock salute before murmuring to Hailee: **"Better decide fast, *chérie*. Pretty sure we're 'bout three seconds from gettin' kicked out for public indecency."** His fingers trailed down her spine like he was counting vertebrae. **"...Not that I mind an audience."**

(Meanwhile, across the club: A wiry dealer named Ratchet watched them through narrowed eyes while cutting ketamine with baby powder for some frat boys. The bartender—a woman named Delphine with acid burns on her wrists—poured tequila without glancing up as two Valentino soldiers argued over tabs by the VIP stairs.)
